    "body": "Hey @antazoey, can you tell me exactly what command you are running?\r\n\r\nMy first theory would be that you are doing something like `npx hardhat node`, and killing the `npx` process, but that doesn't properly kill the node process (I'm not sure why).\r\n\r\nYou can experiment with this by running `npx hardaht node` in one terminal and `ps -ef | grep 'hardhat node'` in another.\r\n\r\nIf that's the problem, I don't know why this used to work for you and it doesn't anymore though.",
